TITLE: Creating Basic Scene Components in Babylon.js
DESCRIPTION: Creates a basic 3D scene with an ArcRotateCamera, HemisphericLight, and a box mesh. The scene is initialized with essential components required for rendering 3D content.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babylonjs/documentation/blob/master/content/features/introductionToFeatures/chap1/first_scene.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const scene = new BABYLON.Scene(engine);

const camera = new BABYLON.ArcRotateCamera("camera", -Math.PI / 2, Math.PI / 2.5, 3, new BABYLON.Vector3(0, 0, 0), scene);
camera.attachControl(canvas, true);

const light = new BABYLON.HemisphericLight("light", new BABYLON.Vector3(0, 1, 0), scene);

const box = BABYLON.MeshBuilder.CreateBox("box", {}, scene);
```

