DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to directly manipulate lattice control points in the lattice's 3D data array to deform a mesh, such as making the mesh pointy at the top. Requires an instantiated lattice with known resolution parameters. Iterates over control points and adjusts their y values.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babylonjs/documentation/blob/master/content/features/featuresDeepDive/mesh/transforms/lattice.md#2025-04-23_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
   // Make it pointy
    for (x = 0; x < lattice.resolutionX; x++) {
        for (z = 0; z < lattice.resolutionZ; z++) {
            const control = lattice.data[x][lattice.resolutionY - 1][z];
