TITLE: Creating a Complete WebXR Scene with Floor Meshes
DESCRIPTION: This snippet creates a complete Babylon.js scene with WebXR support and floor mesh configuration. It includes a basic scene setup with a sphere, lighting, and environment, then adds WebXR functionality with the ground designated as a floor mesh for proper movement in VR.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babylonjs/documentation/blob/master/content/features/featuresDeepDive/webXR/introToWebXR.md#2025-04-23_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var createScene = async function () {
  var scene = new BABYLON.Scene(engine);
  var camera = new BABYLON.FreeCamera("camera1", new BABYLON.Vector3(0, 5, -10), scene);
  camera.setTarget(BABYLON.Vector3.Zero());
  camera.attachControl(canvas, true);
  var light = new BABYLON.HemisphericLight("light1", new BABYLON.Vector3(0, 1, 0), scene);
  light.intensity = 0.7;
  var sphere = BABYLON.MeshBuilder.CreateSphere("sphere1", { segments: 16, diameter: 2 }, scene);
  sphere.position.y = 1;

  const env = scene.createDefaultEnvironment();

  // here we add XR support
  const xr = await scene.createDefaultXRExperienceAsync({
    floorMeshes: [env.ground],
  });

  return scene;
};
```

