TITLE: Initializing a Basic Flow Graph for Console Logging in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates the basic setup of a Babylon.js Flow Graph. It creates a coordinator, a graph, and a context. It then adds a `FlowGraphSceneReadyEventBlock` to trigger execution when the scene loads and a `FlowGraphConsoleLogBlock` to output 'Hello, world!' to the console. The `done` output of the scene ready block is connected to the `in` input of the log block, establishing the execution flow. Finally, `coord.start()` activates the graph.
