TITLE: Modifying Ribbon Path Data for Morphing in Babylon.js
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to modify the coordinate data within an existing `pathArray` used to define a ribbon mesh. The `updatePath` function iterates through the points in a single path and updates their `y` coordinate based on a sine function. The outer loop then applies this function to every path within the `pathArray`. This prepares the data for updating the ribbon mesh geometry.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babylonjs/documentation/blob/master/content/features/featuresDeepDive/mesh/dynamicMeshMorph.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const updatePath = function (path) {
  for (let i = 0; i < path.length; i++) {
    const x = path[i].x;
    const z = path[i].z;
    const y = 20 * Math.sin(i / 10);
    path[i].x = x;
    path[i].y = y;
    path[i].z = z;
  }
};

// update pathArray
for (let p = 0; p < pathArray.length; p++) {
  updatePath(pathArray[p]);
}
```

