TITLE: Dynamic Terrain Color Map Generation in BabylonJS
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates creation of terrain data and color maps with noise generation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babylonjs/documentation/blob/master/content/communityExtensions/dynamicTerrains.md#2025-04-23_snippet_18

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const mapSubX = 1000;
const mapSubZ = 800;
const seed = 0.3;
noise.seed(seed);
const mapData = new Float32Array(mapSubX * mapSubZ * 3);
const mapColors = new Float32Array(mapSubX * mapSubZ * 3);
for (const l = 0; l < mapSubZ; l++) {
  for (const w = 0; w < mapSubX; w++) {
    const x = (w - mapSubX * 0.5) * 5.0;
    const z = (l - mapSubZ * 0.5) * 2.0;
    const y = noise.simplex2(x, z);

    mapData[3 * (l * mapSubX + w)] = x;
    mapData[3 * (l * mapSubX + w) + 1] = y;
    mapData[3 * (l * mapSubX + w) + 2] = z;

    mapColors[3 * (l * mapSubX + w)] = 0.5 + Math.random() * 0.2;
    mapColors[3 * (l * mapSubX + w) + 1] = 0.5 + Math.random() * 0.4;
    mapColors[3 * (l * mapSubX + w) + 2] = 0.5;
  }
}
```

