TITLE: Vertex Shader with Bone and Instance Support in Babylon.js
DESCRIPTION: This GLSL vertex shader includes support for bone animations and instances, demonstrating how to handle these effects when replacing materials with custom shaders.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babylonjs/documentation/blob/master/content/features/featuresDeepDive/postProcesses/renderTargetTextureMultiPass.md#2025-04-23_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: glsl
CODE:
```
precision highp float;

attribute vec3 position;
attribute vec2 uv;

uniform mat4 view;
uniform mat4 projection;
uniform mat4 worldViewProjection;

varying vec2 vUV;

#include<bonesDeclaration>
#include<instancesDeclaration>

void main() {
    vec3 positionUpdated = position;

    #include<instancesVertex>
    #include<bonesVertex>

    vec4 worldPos = finalWorld * vec4(positionUpdated, 1.0);

    vUV = uv;

    gl_Position = projection * view * worldPos;
}
```

