TITLE: Implementing updateParticleVertex Function in Babylon.js SPS
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to implement the updateParticleVertex function for a Solid Particle System. The function is called for each vertex of each particle, allowing per-vertex manipulation of position, color, and UV mapping based on particle properties.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babylonjs/documentation/blob/master/content/features/featuresDeepDive/particles/solid_particle_system/sps_vertices.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
SPS.computeParticleVertex = true; // false by default for performance reason
SPS.updateParticleVertex = function(particle, vertex, v) {
  // particle : the current particle object
  // vertex : the current vertex, a solidParticleVertex object
  // the index of the current vertex in the particle shape
  // example :
  if (particle.shapeID == 1) {
    vertex.position.x *= Math.random() + 1;
    vertex.position.y *= Math.random() + 1;
    vertex.position.z *= Math.random() + 1;
    vertex.color.r = Math.abs(Math.sin(v));
    vertex.color.g = 1 - vertex.color.r
    vertex.uv.x = particle.idx + v;
    vertex.uv.y = vertex.uv.x;
  }

};
```

