TITLE: Loading and Positioning the Bowling Ball Mesh in Babylon.js (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This asynchronous function `createBall` loads a bowling ball mesh from the specified asset path using `BABYLON.ImportMeshAsync`. It then scales the loaded mesh (`result.meshes[1]`) down by a factor of 0.2 and positions it at coordinates (0, 0.5, -5) in the scene. Requires the Babylon.js library, an `Assets` object containing mesh paths, and a `scene` object.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babylonjs/documentation/blob/master/content/guidedLearning/workshop/Bowling.md#2025-04-23_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
async function createBall(scene) {
  const result = await BABYLON.ImportMeshAsync(Assets.meshes.bowlingBall_glb.rootUrl + Assets.meshes.bowlingBall_glb.filename, scene);
  const bowlingBall = result.meshes[1];
  bowlingBall.scaling.scaleInPlace(0.2);
  bowlingBall.position = new BABYLON.Vector3(0, 0.5, -5);
}

createBall(scene);
```

