TITLE: Mixing Textures in GLSL Fragment Shader
DESCRIPTION: A more complex GLSL fragment shader (`custom.fragment.fx`) that samples colors from two textures (`dirt` and `grass`) defined as `sampler2D` uniforms. It uses the built-in `mix` function to blend the texture colors equally based on texture coordinates (`vUV`) and assigns the result to `gl_FragColor`.
