TITLE: Implementing WebXR Polyfill in Babylon.js
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to add the WebXR polyfill to your project for browsers that support WebVR but not WebXR. It creates a Promise that resolves once the polyfill is loaded and initialized, ensuring WebXR API compatibility.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babylonjs/documentation/blob/master/content/features/featuresDeepDive/webXR/introToWebXR.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const xrPolyfillPromise = new Promise((resolve) => {
    if (navigator.xr) {
        return resolve();
    }
    if (window.WebXRPolyfill) {
        new WebXRPolyfill();
        return resolve();
    } else {
        const url = "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/webxr-polyfill@latest/build/webxr-polyfill.js";
        const s = document.createElement("script");
        s.src = url;
        document.head.appendChild(s);
        s.onload = () => {
            new WebXRPolyfill();
            resolve();
        };
    }
});
```

