TITLE: Counter-Clockwise Vector Rotation About Any Point
DESCRIPTION: Formula for S⁺, a counter-clockwise 60° rotation of position vector xi⃗ + yj⃗ about point ai⃗ + bj⃗ on an isometric grid. The rotation is performed by translating to origin, rotating, and translating back.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babylonjs/documentation/blob/master/content/guidedLearning/workshop/Geodesic_Math.md#2025-04-23_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: math
CODE:
```
S⁺(xi⃗ + yj⃗, ai⃗ + bj⃗) = R⁺((xi⃗ + yj⃗) - (ai⃗ + bj⃗)) + ai⃗ + bj⃗ = R⁺((x - a)i⃗) + (y - b)j⃗) + ai⃗ + bj⃗ = -(y - b)i⃗ + ((x - a) + (y - b))j⃗ + ai⃗ + bj⃗ = (a + b - y)i⃗ + (x + y - a)j⃗
```

