TITLE: Implementing Pointer Event Handler in BabylonJS
DESCRIPTION: Sets up a pointer observable to detect click events in the scene. Uses a switch statement to handle POINTERDOWN events and checks if the clicked object was hit before calling the pointer down handler.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babylonjs/documentation/blob/master/content/features/introductionToFeatures/chap6/onoff.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
let switched = false;  //on off flag

scene.onPointerObservable.add((pointerInfo) => {      		
    switch (pointerInfo.type) {
		case BABYLON.PointerEventTypes.POINTERDOWN:
			if(pointerInfo.pickInfo.hit) {
                pointerDown(pointerInfo.pickInfo.pickedMesh)
            }
		break;
    }
});
```

