TITLE: Generating Custom UV Map Data for Dynamic Terrain in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This code populates a data map with no elevation and creates a UV map as a flat array. It sets the u and v values in the 2D texture relative to the (x, z) coordinates of each map point.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babylonjs/documentation/blob/master/content/communityExtensions/dynamicTerrains.md#2025-04-23_snippet_21

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const mapData = new Float32Array(mapSubX * mapSubZ * 3); // x3 float values per point: x, y and z
const mapUVs = new Float32Array(mapSubX * mapSubZ * 2); // x2 because 2 values per point: u, v
for (const l = 0; l < mapSubZ; l++) {
  for (const w = 0; w < mapSubX; w++) {
    const x = (w - mapSubX * 0.5) * 2.0;
    const z = (l - mapSubZ * 0.5) * 2.0;

    mapData[3 * (l * mapSubX + w)] = x;
    mapData[3 * (l * mapSubX + w) + 1] = 0.0;
    mapData[3 * (l * mapSubX + w) + 2] = z;

    mapUVs[2 * (l * mapSubX + w)] = w / mapSubX; // u
    mapUVs[2 * (l * mapSubX + w) + 1] = l / mapSubZ; // v
  }
}
```

