TITLE: Defining a Custom Shader with Uniforms and Samplers in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to define a custom shader using EffectWrapper that includes custom uniforms (`colorOffset`) and samplers (`otherTexture`) in addition to the defaults. These must be declared in the `uniformNames` and `samplerNames` arrays.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babylonjs/documentation/blob/master/content/features/featuresDeepDive/controls/imageFilter.md#2025-04-23_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const customEffectWrapper = new EffectWrapper({
  name: "Custom",
  engine: customFilter.engine,
  fragmentShader: `
        varying vec2 vUV;

        // Default Sampler
        uniform sampler2D textureSampler;

        // Custom uniforms
        uniform sampler2D otherTexture;
        uniform vec3 colorOffset;

        const vec2 scale = vec2(0.25, 1.);

        void main(void) 
        {
            gl_FragColor = texture2D(textureSampler, vUV);

            // Swizzle channels
            float r = gl_FragColor.r;
            gl_FragColor.r = gl_FragColor.b;
            gl_FragColor.b = r;
            gl_FragColor.rgb += clamp(colorOffset, 0., 1.);

            gl_FragColor.rgb *= texture2D(otherTexture, vUV * scale).rgb;
        }
    `,
  // Defines the list of existing samplers (default + customs).
  samplerNames: ["textureSampler", "otherTexture"],
  // Defines the list of existing uniform to be bound.
  uniformNames: ["colorOffset"],
});
```

