TITLE: Configuring Rollup manualChunks for Babylon.js Module Grouping (Function) (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet shows a Rollup configuration using a function for the `output.manualChunks` option. The function inspects the module `id` (path) and returns a chunk name (`webgpu-shaders`, `webgl-shaders`, `webgpu-extensions`, `babylonjs`) if the ID matches specific patterns related to Babylon.js modules. This allows for manual control over chunk creation, similar to Webpack's `cacheGroups`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babylonjs/documentation/blob/master/content/setup/support/asyncChunks.md#2025-04-23_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
```javascript
export default {
  // ...
  output: {
    dir: "output",
    manualChunks: (id) => {
      if (id.includes("ShadersWGSL")) {
        return "webgpu-shaders";
      } else if (id.includes("Shaders")) {
        return "webgl-shaders";
      } else if (id.includes("WebGPU")) {
        return "webgpu-extensions";
      } else if (id.includes("babylonjs")) {
        return "babylonjs";
      }
    },
  },
};
```
