TITLE: Creating Terrain Data Map with Sine/Cosine Function in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Generates a terrain height map using sine and cosine functions to create rolling hills. The map data is stored in a Float32Array with x, y, z coordinates for each point.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babylonjs/documentation/blob/master/content/communityExtensions/dynamicTerrains/DTExamples.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const mapSubX = 100;
const mapSubZ = 100;
const mapData = new Float32Array(mapSubX * mapSubZ * 3);
for (let l = 0; l < mapSubZ; l++) {
  for (let w = 0; w < mapSubX; w++) {
    mapData[3 * (l * mapSubX + w)] = (w - mapSubX * 0.5) * 2.0;
    mapData[3 * (l * mapSubX + w) + 1] = (w / (l + 1)) * Math.sin(l / 2) * Math.cos(w / 2) * 2.0;
    mapData[3 * (l * mapSubX + w) + 2] = (l - mapSubZ * 0.5) * 2.0;
  }
}
```

