TITLE: Workaround for Passing Samplers Using #define inline in GLSL (WebGPU)
DESCRIPTION: Shows the workaround for the WebGPU limitation of passing samplers to functions in GLSL shaders. By adding the `#define inline` directive before the function definition, Babylon.js's pre-pass shader code inliner is instructed to replace calls to this function with the function's actual code body during shader processing. This avoids the WebGPU compilation error related to passing samplers as arguments.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babylonjs/documentation/blob/master/content/setup/support/webGPU/webGPUBreakingChanges.md#2025-04-23_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: glsl
CODE:
```
#define inline
vec4 getPixel(sampler2D sampler, vec2 uv) {
    return texture2D(sampler, uv);
}
```

