TITLE: Computing Animation Offset for VATs with Thin Instances
DESCRIPTION: This function calculates the correct offset for VATs with thin instances to ensure each instance starts its animation at the intended time. This is necessary because multiple instances often share the same BakedVertexAnimationManager.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babylonjs/documentation/blob/master/content/features/featuresDeepDive/animation/baked_texture_animations.md#2025-04-23_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
function computeOffset(
  fromFrame: number,
  toFrame: number,
  time: number,
  fps: number = 60
): number {
  const totalFrames = toFrame - fromFrame + 1;
  const t = time * fps / totalFrames;
  const frame = Math.floor((t - Math.floor(t)) * totalFrames);
  return totalFrames - frame;
}
```

