TITLE: Constructing Open Curve Track Points (Babylon.js, JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Generates points along an open path (three-quarters of a circle) by varying the angle in the trigonometric functions. The final points array defines the open curve, suitable for drawing or animating a carriage. This approach is applicable where full closure is not required, and complements closed track construction.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babylonjs/documentation/blob/master/content/guidedLearning/workshop/Track.md#2025-04-23_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var points = [];
var n = 375; // number of points
var r = 20; //radius
for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {
  points.push(new BABYLON.Vector3(r * Math.cos((i * 3 * Math.PI) / (2 * n)), 0, r * Math.sin((i * 3 * Math.PI) / (2 * n))));
}
```

