TITLE: Animated Dynamic Terrain with Time-Based Animation in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to create an animated terrain that updates every frame using a custom vertex function. This example creates a moving wave pattern based on time.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babylonjs/documentation/blob/master/content/communityExtensions/dynamicTerrains.md#2025-04-23_snippet_35

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const t = 0.0;
terrain.useCustomVertexFunction = true;
terrain.refreshEveryFrame = true;
terrain.computeNormals = true;

// user custom function: now the elevation depends on t too.
