TITLE: Implementing Event Listener Pattern in TypeScript for Vaporwear 3D Experience
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates the implementation of an event listener pattern for handling hotspots and configuration loading in the Vaporwear 3D experience. It emulates the addEventListener pattern from the DOM.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babylonjs/documentation/blob/master/content/guidedLearning/devStories/vaporwearConfigurator/3d.md#2025-04-23_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
public addEventListener(type: string, callback: (data: any) => void) {
    switch (type) {
        case "hotspot-hover":
            this._hotspotHoverCallbacks.push(callback);
            break;
        case "hotspot-click":
            this._hotspotClickCallbacks.push(callback);
            break;
        case "config-loaded":
            this._configLoadedCallbacks.push(callback);
            break;
    }
}
```

