TITLE: Executing Geodesic Polyhedron Generation Sequence in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates the sequence of function calls required to generate the complete Geodesic Polyhedron data. It initializes a `Primary` object (`PT`), calculates coefficients and inner facets, determines edge vectors (ABOB), calculates rotated vectors for other overlaps (OBOA, BAOA), and then iterates through each face (`f`) of the base structure (`IDATA`). Inside the loop, it maps the face, adds inner facets to `GDmnDATA`, and conditionally adds overlap facets (ABOB, OBOA, or BAOA) based on edge matching information stored in `IDATA.edgematch`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babylonjs/documentation/blob/master/content/guidedLearning/workshop/Geodesic_Code.md#2025-04-23_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
PT = CreatePrimary(m, n);
   PT.SetIndices();
   PT.CalcCoeffs();
   PT.InnerFacets();
   PT.EdgeVecsABOB();
   PT.ABOBtoOBOA();
   PT.ABOBtoBAOA();
   for (f = 0; f < IDATA.face.length; f++) {
       PT.MapToFace(f);
       PT.InnerToGDmnData(f);
       if(IDATA.edgematch[f][1] === "B") {
            PT.ABOBtoGDmnDATA(f);
       };
       if(IDATA.edgematch[f][1] === "O") {
            PT.OBOAtoGDmnDATA(f);
       };
       if(IDATA.edgematch[f][3] === "A") {
            PT.BAOAtoGDmnDATA(f);
       };
   };
```

