TITLE: Implementing Frame-by-Frame Animation Loop in Babylon.js (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Sets up an animation loop using `scene.registerAfterRender`. In each frame, it updates the `carriage` position and rotation, and optionally the `contents` rotation (if not freight), using pre-calculated data from `carriagePositions`, `carriageRotations`, and `passengerRotations` arrays. The index `i` cycles through the animation steps.
SOURCE: https://github.com/babylonjs/documentation/blob/master/content/guidedLearning/workshop/Track.md#2025-04-23_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
i = 0;
var nbSteps = carriagePositions.length;
var animate = true;
scene.registerAfterRender(function () {
  carrriage.position = carriagePositions[i];
  carrriage.rotationQuaternion = carriageRotations[i];
  if (!isFreight) {
    contents.rotationQuaternion = passengerRotations[i];
  }

  i += 1;
  i %= nbSteps;
});
```

